  "prompt": "What features made the first iPhone so revolutionary?",
  "response": "The first iPhone, introduced by Steve Jobs in 2007, was revolutionary for several key reasons:\n\n1. Touchscreen interface\n- Full touchscreen with multi-touch technology\n- No physical keyboard, which was unique at the time\n- Intuitive gesture-based interactions\n\n2. User interface design\n- Simple, clean, and user-friendly\n- Large, high-resolution display\n- Smooth scrolling and animations\n\n3. Internet capabilities\n- Full web browsing experience on a mobile device\n- Safari web browser that worked like a desktop browser\n- Ability to view full websites, not just mobile versions\n\n4. Visual voicemail\n- Users could choose which voicemails to listen to\n- Broke away from traditional linear voicemail systems\n\n5. Integration of multiple functions\n- Combined phone, internet browser, music player, and email device\n- Eliminated need to carry multiple devices\n\n6. App ecosystem potential\n- Introduced the concept of mobile apps\n- App Store launched in 2008, creating a new software marketplace\n\n7. Sensors and hardware\n- Accelerometer for screen rotation\n- Proximity sensor\n- High-quality touchscreen\n- Sleek, minimalist design\n\nThese features fundamentally changed mobile computing and set the standard for smartphones that followed.",
